  "prompt": "How is the movie \"Happy New Year\"?",
  "response": "\"Happy New Year\" is a 2014 Indian action-comedy film directed by Farah Khan and stars an ensemble cast including Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone, Abhishek Bachchan, Boman Irani, Sonu Sood, and Vivaan Shah. The film revolves around a group of misfits who come together to pull off a heist during a prestigious dance competition in Dubai.\n\nThe film combines elements of action, comedy, and drama, with an emphasis on themes of friendship, trust, and redemption. It features several musical numbers and grand production values, typical of Farah Khan's style, along with colorful visuals and energetic performances.\n\n\"Happy New Year\" received mixed reviews from critics, with some praising its entertaining nature and performances, particularly that of Shah Rukh Khan, while others criticized its length and formulaic plot. However, it was commercially successful, drawing large audiences in theaters, both in India and overseas.\n\nOverall, if you enjoy action-packed comedies with a mix of dance and drama, \"Happy New Year\" might be worth watching for its entertainment value and star power.",
